  "texts": [
    "Frechet distance, also known as Wasserstein-2 distance, is used to determine how far apart these two distributions are.The inception score provides an evaluation of the quality of a set of synthetic pictures based on how effectively they are classified as one of 1,000 known items by the state-ofthe-art image classification algorithm Inception v3.",
    "The scores are a sum of the marginal probability integral and the quality of the conditional class predictions for each synthetic picture (diversity).",
    "The purpose of creating the FID score is to compare the statistical characteristics of a set of synthetic photos to those of a set of real images from the target domain.",
    "To better capture the similarity of produced pictures to genuine ones, the \"Fréchet Inception Distance\" (FID) was established for evaluating the effectiveness of GANs at image production better than IS(Inspection Score).",
    "Datasets for different GAN modelsThe datasets used for training and testing Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) have a major influence on their performance and generalization."
